-- Democratic Party's Kaieda Hints He May Challenge Kan in Leadership Vote
-- Shunichi Ozasa
-- 2010-08-01T05:39:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-08-01/democratic-party-s-kaieda-hints-he-may-challenge-kan-in-leadership-vote.html

          
          
             Banri Kaieda, a member of Japan’s
ruling Democratic Party of Japan, may challenge Prime Minister
Naoto Kan for the party chief’s post at an election in
September, the lawmaker hinted on a news program on Fuji
Television network today.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
Kanoko Matsuyama in Tokyo at 
 kmatsuyama2@bloomberg.net   
          
          


  


        